Samples from existing databases

Source: R/functions_v_0_2_13.R
sample_age_wt.Rd

Sampling from the loaded objects nhanes.filtered, who.expand, cdc.expand, or no sampling at all ("None").

Usage

sample_age_wt(
  df_name = "None",
  nsubj = 20,
  lower.agemo = 18 * 12,
  upper.agemo = 65 * 12,
  lower.wt = 0,
  upper.wt = 100,
  prop.male = 0.5,
  seed.number = 1234
)

Arguments

df_name

Name of databases, either "None", "CDC", "WHO", or "NHANES"

nsubj

Number of subjects

lower.agemo

Min Age (months) not applicable for "None"

upper.agemo

Max Age (months) not applicable for "None"

lower.wt

Min WT (kg) not applicable for "None"

upper.wt

Max WT (kg) not applicable for "None"

prop.male

Proportion of males (e.g. 0.5) not applicable for "None"

seed.number

seed number

Value

a dataframe with nsubj number of rows
